    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks, this is a good start. i think it's a bit too generic though. i want to add a line that acknowledges how much we actually appreciated their specific expertise in cloud architecture, just to make it feel more personalized and less like a robot sent it. can you rewrite it to include a specific mention of their cloud architecture skills being impressive, while maintaining that professional tone?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That's a smart move; personalization is key, even when delivering bad news. You want them to feel seen, not just processed like a pile of resumes. I can certainly weave in a specific nod to their cloud architecture skills. It's much better than just saying \"good job,\" which is what most of the other candidates probably heard!\n\nHere is the revised draft, with a specific mention of their cloud architecture prowess. It feels much more tailored, like a seasoned, albeit slightly-too-busy, manager wrote it.\n\n***\n\n**Subject: Update on the Senior Developer Role at [Company Name]**\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview with us for the Senior Developer position. We truly enjoyed getting to know you and learning more about your impressive technical skills during the final round. In fact, your deep expertise in cloud architecture was particularly striking to the team—it was truly impressive to see how you approach complex systems.\n\nThe caliber of candidates we saw was incredibly high, which made this a very difficult decision for the entire team. We wanted to let you know that we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose specific experience aligned slightly closer to the immediate needs of this",
      "source": "target",
